<br>
However, lately, I'm starting to see threads that people start to condemn someone that have no substance or complaint attached.  They're just &quot;So-and-so is a KSer/camp stealer/ninjalooter/dolphinlover/d00d/whatever and you all should put him on ignore.&quot;<br>
<br>
Often enough, the accused are stupid and inept, unable to put a coherent thought together to defend themselves here (if and) when they do so.<br>
<br>
But, and I only speak for myself, this &quot;mob mentality&quot; disturbs me.  For me, the burden of proof remains on the accuser.<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm missing something, but the post about Xxmike and Yonly exemplifies what I'm discussing.  There's no substantial allegation there, only the initial poster's request that the rest of us put them on /ignore.  Why?  No reason given--not even &quot;he's a KSer/camp-stealer/etc&quot;.  Again, maybe I'm missing something--maybe there's another thread somewhere else where the allegations lie, but I haven't found it (nor do I especially want to go digging for it--you want me to condemn/shun someone, you'd better damn well do the work yourself to convince me I should).<br>
<br>
Think about it before you jump on the bandwagon.  Just because someone's a poor writer, a poor thinker, and a downright bad-roleplayer, should he or she be condemned on the basis of someone's word and their word alone, no actual accusation of wrong-doing that can be defended against? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/LASLAN.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->andersonrob@earthlink.net<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/index.html<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->EverQuest: Lasgalen Lothir, Firiona Vie server</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buvin>Buvin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>the ever dying ranger</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/03 11:08:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2864.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: He did WHAT?!  Get 'im!!!</span><hr size=1> I don't think most people run here on the first occurrence.<br>
<br>
Ok, sometimes people get fed up too easy and come and post stuff they probably shouldn't. Heck, I've done that...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessage?topicID=2697.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...2697.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
